package wohl:matter-compose@0.1.0;

/// The host-bound seam for the verified Matter core, modelled on the
/// spar-generated `matter-ports` interface (Wohl_Matter::MatterBridgeProcess
/// → spar/generated/matter.wit). It carries the two host dependencies the
/// core cannot self-supply in the sandbox:
///
///   - transport (= rs-matter NetworkReceive / NetworkSend): on-message-in
///     returns the next inbound packet (none = nothing yet, doubling as the
///     availability check) and emit-message-out sends one. `channel` tags the
///     two-party loopback (0 = to device, 1 = to controller), which the
///     single-instance spar port does not need.
///   - clock (= spar on-clock_in / monotonictime): on-clock-in returns host
///     monotonic time in microseconds, driving the core's embassy-time driver.
///     The core no longer reads std::time directly — time crosses the WIT seam.
///
/// NOTE on spar fidelity: spar's generated matter.wit references undefined
/// types (mattermessage / monotonictime / entropybytes / bytes) and uses mixed
/// hyphen/underscore identifiers (`on-message_in`), so it is not directly
/// bindable; this seam mirrors its shape with valid WIT (list<u8> for
/// mattermessage, u64 µs for monotonictime). Entropy (spar on-entropy_in) is
/// the remaining seam to route across — see SWV-MATTER-002 C4b.
interface matter-ports {
    /// Next inbound Matter packet on `channel`, or none. (NetworkReceive)
    on-message-in: func(channel: u8) -> option<list<u8>>;
    /// Send one Matter packet on `channel`. (NetworkSend)
    emit-message-out: func(channel: u8, data: list<u8>);
    /// Host monotonic time in microseconds. (clock seam)
    on-clock-in: func() -> u64;
}

/// Drives the verified core. `run` completes a full PASE handshake and
/// returns true on success. An interface (not a bare world func): the
/// rules_wasm_component bindgen rule generates a duplicate world-export
/// symbol for bare world funcs (E0255), so the components use interface
/// exports. `wasmtime run --invoke 'run()'` still reaches it.
interface runner {
    run: func() -> bool;
}

/// Host shell: owns the packet queues + the monotonic clock, exports the seam.
world transport {
    export matter-ports;
}

/// Verified Matter core: imports the seam, exports the runner.
world matter-core {
    import matter-ports;
    export runner;
}
